#: ../../E/ENQ.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from the ASCII mnemonic ENQuire for 0000101] An on-line convention for "
"querying someone's availability. After opening a :ref:`talk-mode` connection"
" to someone apparently in heavy hack mode, one might type :code:`SYN SYN "
"ENQ?` (the SYNs representing notional synchronization bytes), and expect a "
"return of :ref:`ACK` or :ref:`NAK` depending on whether or not the person "
"felt interruptible. Compare :ref:`ping`\\, :ref:`finger`\\, and the usage of"
" :code:`FOO?` listed under :ref:`talk-mode`\\."
msgstr ""
"[0000101を表すASCIIの覚え方ENQuireより] "
"誰かの応答可能性を問い合わせるためのオンライン上の慣習。どうやら本気のハックモードに入っているらしい相手に\\ :ref:`talk-mode`\\ "
"接続を開いたあと、\\ :code:`SYN SYN ENQ?`\\ "
"(SYNは仮想的な同期バイトを表す)と打ち込み、相手が割り込み可能と感じているかどうかに応じて\\ :ref:`ACK`\\ または\\ "
":ref:`NAK`\\ が返ってくることを期待する、というわけである。\\ :ref:`ping`\\ 、\\ :ref:`finger`\\ "
"や、\\ :ref:`talk-mode`\\ の項に挙げた\\ :code:`FOO?`\\ の用法と比較せよ。"
